description: Why does human perception of time seem to vary across situations? How many times have you or a friend commented that the days seem to fly by now that you‚Äôre older? Laura L. Carstensen, Ph.D. and others have developed a Socioemotional Sensitivity Theory (SST) to help understand how humans monitor time and their own lifetime. Central to this theory is the idea of perceived time horizons (how much time is left on life) exerts a strong influence on motivation, goals, and preferences. The less time you perceive you have left to live, the faster time seems to go and the more humans tend to focus on activities that have emotional meaning and satisfaction. https://psycnet.apa.org/fulltext/2018-31242-007.pdf #ThisIsNIH

‚Ä¢	Stay out of the water if you‚Äôve had diarrhea in the last two weeks to help protect others from infectious germs.‚†Ä
‚Ä¢	Try not to swallow recreational water.‚†Ä
‚Ä¢	Avoid swimming or playing near places where storm water is released on the beach.‚†Ä
‚Ä¢	Stay out of the water for at least 24 hours after a storm.‚†Ä
‚Ä¢	Always wash your hands before you eat or drink.‚†Ä

description:
September is Suicide Prevention Month. Suicide is complicated and tragic, but it is often preventable. @nimhgov's Dr. Shelli Avenevoli explains the warning signs of suicide and how to get help. If you or someone you know is in immediate crisis, call or text the 988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline at 988. The Lifeline provides 24-hour, confidential support to anyone in suicidal crisis or emotional distress. Call 911 in life-threatening situations. Learn more about the signs of suicide at nimh.nih.gov/suicideprevention. @988lifeline

description:
These cilia are "doing the wave"! Cilia are hair-like biological structures made up of more than 600 different proteins that work together with hundreds of others in a tightly-packed layer to create movement. Their synchronized motion helps sweep mucus from the lungs and usher eggs from the ovaries into the uterus. By controlling how fluid flows around an embryo, cilia also help ensure that organs like the heart develop on the correct side of your body. Cilia are tiny but mighty!

Credit: Zvonimir Dogic, @brandeisuniversity
.

.

description:
Today‚Äôs ruling by the US Supreme Court on #AffirmativeAction is disappointing and unfortunately continues to challenge this country on issues of racial and health equity.

As a private health foundation, we know all too well that when it comes to your health in the United States, your zip code is more important than your genetic code. This dismaying correlation is attributable to our nation‚Äôs history of structural racism -- forms of residential apartheid and segregation ‚Äì playing out in the conditions of how families and communities of color work, live, and play. Health is about neighborhoods, housing, jobs, and education. Affirmative Action policies were constructed as a tool to help tilt the playing field as a counterweight to decades and centuries of the gravity of racism in policy and practice.

Our Supreme Court should serve as the arbiter of equal justice under the law. It should not act in a manner that further excludes the most vulnerable from the reach of our laws, our Constitution, and meaningful opportunity. At this moment, here at The California Endowment, we stand resolutely and unapologetically with the visionaries and warriors for social and racial justice whose work we invest in and support. ‚ÄúLa Lucha continua‚Äù ‚Äì the Fight continues.

.
We need to come together as a community and try to find solutions. We need to work with both Muslim and Non-Muslim parents and educate children. We need to work with our schools and Mosques. This is an everyday issue, we can‚Äôt let our children #suffer in silence or feel embarrassed or shy away from this topic. Speak to your #children ask them if they are okay and tell them not to ignore everyday insults but to speak up so that we can #report these #hate #crimes to the police.
.
